  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">• The JET 14 MeV neutron calibration requires a neutron generator to be deployed inside the vacuum vessel by means of the remote handling system. • A neutron generator of suitable intensity and compliant with physics, remote handling and safety requirements has been identified and procured.The scientific programme of the preparatory phase devoted to fully characterizing the selected 14 MeV neutron generator is discussed. • The aim is to measure the absolute neutron emission rate within (± 5%) and the energy spectrum of emitted neutron as a function of angles. • The physics preparations, source issues, safety and engineering aspects required to calibrate directly the JET neutron detectors are discussed.</subfield>
